    "body": "### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.8.0-dev-984-g568737d5b3\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nvim doesn't support the feature\n\n### Operating system/version\n\narchlinux\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nfoot version: 1.13.1\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nfoot\n\n### Installation\n\nAUR\n\n### How to reproduce the issue\n\n```lua\r\nlocal ns = vim.api.nvim_create_namespace(\"test-ns\")\r\nlocal opts = {\r\n\tvirt_lines = {\r\n\t\t{{\"text\", \"teststyle\"}}\r\n\t},\r\n}\r\nvim.api.nvim_buf_set_extmark(0, ns, 7, 0, opts)\r\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nThe virtual line should render because the line it's within the buffer.\n\n### Actual behavior\n\nThe virtual line doesn't render at all and doesn't show any errors.",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "I don't think this is a display issue? `nvim_buf_set_extmark()` is 0-indexed. The repro example places a `virt_line` at the 8th buffer line, which doesn't exist. The only problem here perhaps is that it doesn't show an error?",
