            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "I think some of the `ml_line_count` checks in `api/extmark.c:nvim_set_extmark()` should check for `ml_line_count - 1` instead? I.e. this patch (correctly?) shows an error for this repro:\r\n```diff\r\n+++ b/src/nvim/api/extmark.c\r\n@@ -745,12 +745,12 @@ Integer nvim_buf_set_extmark(Buffer buffer, Integer ns_id, Integer line, Integer\r\n   if (line < 0) {\r\n     api_set_error(err, kErrorTypeValidation, \"line value outside range\");\r\n     goto error;\r\n-  } else if (line > buf->b_ml.ml_line_count) {\r\n+  } else if (line >= buf->b_ml.ml_line_count) {\r\n     if (strict) {\r\n       api_set_error(err, kErrorTypeValidation, \"line value outside range\");\r\n       goto error;\r\n     } else {\r\n-      line = buf->b_ml.ml_line_count;\r\n+      line = buf->b_ml.ml_line_count - 1;\r\n     }\r\n   } else if (line < buf->b_ml.ml_line_count) {\r\n     len = ephemeral ? MAXCOL : strlen(ml_get_buf(buf, (linenr_T)line + 1, false));\r\n```",
